Package: mmCTBN
Type: Package
Title: Continuous-Time Bayesian Networks for Multimorbidity in Electronic Health Records
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: 
    person(given = "Oyebayo Ridwan",
           family = "Olaniran",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "ridwan.olaniran@lshtm.ac.uk",
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-7342-8639"))
Maintainer: Oyebayo Ridwan Olaniran <ridwan.olaniran@lshtm.ac.uk>
Description: A unified framework for fitting Continuous-Time Bayesian Networks
    (CTBNs) to multimorbidity data from Electronic Health Records (EHRs).
    The package implements both fully Bayesian (Stan / MCMC) and fast
    Maximum-A-Posteriori (MAP / Laplace) estimators for the same panel-data
    Poisson likelihood, with four prior families: spike-and-slab,
    structured (order-penalised normal), Bayesian LASSO, and regularised
    horseshoe. It supports arbitrary network sizes and interaction orders
    (main effects up to 5-way interactions), generic data simulation for
    any number of nodes, parallel implementation across nodes, K-fold
    cross-validation, and a rich suite of inference and visualisation
    utilities (network graphs, risk trajectories, synergistic
    interaction plots, time-dependent AUC, Brier scores).
